{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5fae0132-133d-451d-ac75-ec7a581dbab5","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- \\\n  --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Key changes** (everything after `--` is forwarded to MTP):\n\n| VSTest | MTP |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to test projects):\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`\n- `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`\n\n**Required project property** (`.csproj` or `Directory.Build.props`):\n```xml\n<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"08b22059-2365-4d7c-b231-7fe844934095","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating a `dotnet test` command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a codebase task. Let me provide the equivalent command.\n\nLet me think about the mapping:\n\n**VSTest command:**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" --logger trx --collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\" --blame-crash --blame-hang --blame-hang-timeout 5m\n```\n\n**Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents:**\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, `dotnet test` still works as the orchestrator, but the options change. In .NET 8 with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, there are some key differences:\n\n\nThe filter syntax remains the same when using `dotnet test` as the orchestrator, though running the test app directly uses the same filter format. For TRX logging, I need the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` NuGet package and then use `--report-trx` instead. Code coverage collection can still work through `dotnet test` with the same `--collect` syntax if using `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` or `coverlet`, though the exact approach depends on which coverage tool is configured.\n\nFor crash and hang diagnostics, `--blame-crash` becomes `--crashdump` (requiring `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump`), and `--blame-hang` with its timeout becomes `--hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m` (requiring `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump`). When using Microsoft.Testing.Platform with `dotnet test`, I pass platform-specific options after a `--` separator, but if running the test executable directly, the options go straight through. I'm working through what the actual command structure looks like when invoking via `dotnet test`. Continuing with the NuGet packages needed for the testing extensions. For .NET 8 specifically with Microsoft.Testing.Platform, I need to enable dotnet test support by setting `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` in the project file, then use `dotnet test` with the `--` separator to forward the MTP options properly.","outputTokens":1299,"requestId":"5C37:3CEFF5:A2C50:CC0F8:69F54AEF"},"id":"8b8bddfd-15ef-4dca-ac24-3ab03bd549da","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:53:24.402Z","parentId":"65e63700-9811-4020-a2b2-989900144660"}
